properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 13 at 1:32AM EST until January 13 at 4:00PM EST by NWS Newport/Morehead City NC
properties.description:
...ELEVATED SEAS WILL CONTINUE THROUGH EARLY WEDNESDAY MORNING...
...DENSE SEA FOG CONTINUES INTO MONDAY AFTERNOON...

.Elevated seas will linger across the waters into early Wednesday
morning. Sea fog will be dense at times into Monday afternoon,
and may continue to plague marine areas through mid week as warm
and humid southwest winds continue to blow over the relatively
cool waters.

* WHAT...For the Dense Fog Advisory, dense fog will reduce
visibility to one quarter to one half mile. For the Small
Craft Advisory, seas 4 to 7 feet.

* WHERE...The coastal waters from Cape Lookout to Surf City.

* WHEN...For the Dense Fog Advisory, until 4 PM EST this
afternoon. For the Small Craft Advisory, until 1 AM EST
Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft. Low
visibility will make navigation difficult.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM EST THIS AFTERNOON... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 AM EST WEDNESDAY
